occupation: Angel Investor & Advisor at Angel Investor
summary:
I'm passionate about helping early stage founders succeed and create meaningful impact for humanity & planet: 

• Co-Founder @BukuWarung (YC S20), empowering 60 million Indonesian MSMEs. Raised $80m, built team of 250+
• Angel Investor & Advisor in 40+ startups
• Director of Product @Carousell, largest second-hand marketplace in SEA
• Product Lead @Grab, PM #8 - drove 21X growth
• Software Engineer @Microsoft, IIT Bombay Computer Science

experiences.title: Angel Investor & Advisor
experiences.description: Angel investor & advisor in 40+ startups in SEA, India

experiences.title: Co-Founder & President
experiences.description: BukuWarung is revolutionizing the way MSMEs in Indonesia manage their businesses through our technology platform. We've raised $80M from top-tier investors globally, including Peter Thiel's Valar Ventures, Goodwater Capital, Y-Combinator, SoftBank Partners, DST Global Partners, and strategic angel investors from Stripe, PayPal, Plaid, Grab, Gojek, Facebook, Airbnb, and Mastercard. Our vision is to empower 60 million MSMEs in Indonesia.

experiences.title: Director of Product
experiences.description: Carousell is the largest mobile classifieds platform in SEA backed by Telenor, Naspers, Sequoia Capital, Rakuten Ventures, 500 Startups and EDBI

experiences.title: Product Lead
experiences.description: As PM #8 at Grab, I led the development of multiple product and engineering teams that delivered key products such as Driver Experience, Driver Acquisition, GrabPay Merchant Payments, and Digital Goods. During my time, played a key role in Grab's hyper-growth, which saw the company scale up to a team of 150 PMs. My contributions were instrumental in Grab's success, including securing several billion-dollar funding rounds, acquiring Uber SE Asia, and transforming into a Super app. I take great pride in my work at Grab, and the impact it had on millions of users across Southeast Asia.

experiences.title: Tech Advisor & Speaker

• Fintech Speaker at ProductCamp'17, Singapore: "Payments in Indonesia: Banking the Un-banked" 

• Mentor at Startupbootcamp: Advised a fintech start-up on their growth strategies and localisation for SEA

• Panelist at Startup Weekend Singapore 2018

• Speaker, "Navigating Complexity when creating Product Roadmaps" (https://generalassemb.ly/education/navigating-complexity-when-creating-product-roadmaps/singapore/59738)

• Contributor to ProductCoLLab (Product Manager community in SG)

• Writer at medium.com/@chinmaychauhan

recommendations:
Ellery Jose, MTM



I was very fortunate to have had the chance to work with Chinmay for the second time, this time in his capacity as BukuWarung's Co-Founder/President and overall Technology leader. He oversaw the scaling up of both the Product, Design and Engineering teams, bringing top-notch people to lead these teams. He is as I remember him from Grab, a very smart product-oriented technical person. He is thoughtful, equally challenging in his questions to his leaders but also deeply empathetic to all who work with him. He is also decisive, can cut through the noise and provide clear direction.

Stuart Thornton



Ive worked with Chinmay in a few capacities. Chinmay was an angel investor in hoolah where he clearly demonstrated his strategic and tactical capabilities with a professional due diligence into our business. This tested our knowledge of the business and contributed to our learning. His capabilities with product leadership was also evident as we began to work with him on more tactical opportunities outside of investment. Ive also been honored to try and return the favour as he set on his startup course - not that he has needed it at all. Smart, sharp, dependable I know success is around the corner for his latest venture.
